  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>By spending a full-round action concentrating, you can merge with a tree, which allows you to travel through trees, roots and branches at your standard movement rate by concentrating as a full-round action each turn.<br><br>While moving, you can freely 'jump' to other trees if their roots or branches are close to each other, and you cannot be damaged as you have no physical presence.<br><br>If a tree you are currently occupying or traveling through takes damage, you take the same amount of damage. You can only 'resurface' once you reach the trunk of another tree. While occupying trees, it is possible to attack creatures standing adjacent to the tree you occupy, and you can easily hide inside a tree that can contain your body, making others suffer a -20 penalty to spot you.</p>\n\n\n\n",
